@@bThe Far-Eastern Approach@@N~
@@yA long, unwavering causeway divides dunes on both sides, the surface compressed by generations of merchants, scouts, and soldiers.
   
@@bSunlight bounces off grains the color of hammered brass, then fades into cool cobalt shade where the drifts shoulder up against stone.
   
@@ySomewhere out in the open waste, canvas rigging snaps in the wind, a faint reminder that this road is still the desert's main artery.@@N
   
@@yThe straight alignment makes travel simple, but the silence beyond the road reminds you how quickly a single step off-course can turn hostile.@@N
   
@@yThis is the final marked stretch before the road narrows and the last cairns give way to open, unmarked desert sand.@@N
